   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_HM28595_1815_06_04_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1815-06-04">Sunday 4 June</date><lb/>
               </dateline>
               <salute>My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1">Francis</persName>,<lb/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">My father</persName> has just heard <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">my mother</persName>
               <lb/>
               read to him your letter of advice to<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#XxxxQ1">Quin</persName> upon the question of his <choice>
                  <orig>return<lb/>
                  ing</orig>
                  <reg>returning</reg>
               </choice> home, and he deputes to me to<lb/>
               tell you how much pleasure it gave<lb/>
               him - I wish I could convey to you<lb/>
               the expression of his countenance &amp;<lb/>
               his own emphatic pronounciation of<lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">Excellent</hi>! - <hi rend="underline">Excellent</hi>! - <hi rend="underline">Admirable!</hi>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I wish you could have seen the pride<lb/>
               as well as pleasure my mother took in<lb/>
               reading it and the delight it gave my<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SneyM1">Aunt Mary</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SneyC1">Aunt Charlotte</persName> &amp; each &amp;<lb/>
                  all of your nieces - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeW1">William</persName> who was<lb/>
                  not in the room when it was read aloud<lb/>
                  has this moment finished it &amp; echoes<lb/>
                  -- (Albeit unused to echo) -- Excellent! -</p>
            <lb/>
            <p>I shall take a copy of it, and beg<lb/>
               your permission to use <add>part of</add> it whenever I<lb/>
               have opportunity to do so for the good<lb/>
               of others - Of course I shall not use your<lb/>
               name - But the sentiment &amp; opinion<lb/>
               of your letter are so entirely our own<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_HM28595_1815_06_04_page02.jpg"/>
               
               &amp; they are so strongly &amp; clearly expressed that<lb/>
               I cannot help wishing to be the means of<lb/>
               making this <hi rend="underline">real</hi> letter advantageous to<lb/>
               other young persons - <hi rend="underline">Reality</hi> has a power<lb/>
               over the mind which fiction never <hi rend="underline">can</hi>
               <lb/>
               &amp; never ought to obtain -</p>
            <lb/>
            <closer>
               Your sincere friend<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1">brother</persName>
                  <lb/>
               I will add nothing to this<lb/>
               valuable letter but our expression of delight<lb/>
               at reading any thing so good as your most<lb/>
               wise and excellent letter to your protegé<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> E.</persName> is much better than he was when<lb/>
               I wrote last -<lb/>
                  The <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#II">Indian</placeName> box is arrived in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  as announced by <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ExxxX1">Elliot</persName> this day.<lb/>
                  How is <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauA1">Alicia</persName>?</p>
               <lb/>
               <closer>
               Ever your affectionate Sister<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">ME</persName>
                  <lb/>
               </closer>
            </postscript>
         </div>
